A 30-year old mechanic, Mohammed Ahmed, was on Thursday arraigned in a Kaduna Chief Magistrates’ Court for allegedly stealing a generator valued at N120,000. Ahmed, who resides near Kawo Market in Kaduna, was arraigned on a three-count charge of criminal breach of trust, cheating and theft. The Prosecutor, Insp. Chidi Leo, told the court that Usman Shuaibu, who resides at Ungwan Sarki, reported the incident at the Kawo Police Station on Aug. 20. According to Leo, sometimes in January 2018, the complainant gave the defendant his generator valued at N120, 000 to repair for which he was charged N8, 500. “When the complainant gave the defendant the generator and the money, he absconded with it. “All efforts to locate him proved abortive until on Aug. 19 he was seen at Kawo Market and arrested.” The offences contravened the Kaduna State Penal Code, Laws, 2017. The defendant, however, pleaded not guilty to the charges. The Magistrate, Mr Ibrahim Emmanuel, granted him bail for N100,000 with one surety in like sum. Emmanuel ordered that the surety must reside within the jurisdiction of the court and adjourned the matter until Sept. 14 for hearing. 